# Palette files are plain text and should be LF-everywhere. The old per-file
# `eol=crlf` directives never actually fired (the files were committed as LF
# and git's smudge filter left them alone), but jj's `eol-conversion = "input"`
# kept flagging the remaining CRLF stragglers as modified. Normalizing here
# makes both git and jj agree without relying on user-level config.
*.hex text eol=lf
